<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-02-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-02-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="87" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-10"><hi rend="italic">February 10,
                                    1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Conger reports that the representatives of France, Germany, Great
                            Britain, and Italy have asked their respective governments that an
                            agreement be suggested to the belligerents not to send any of their
                            troops into Chihli.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>